There are two kinds of memecoins. 
1) viral moment memecoins
2) evergreen memecoins

Viral moment memecoins capitalize on the attention of a viral moment and then die once the moment passes. 
There’s a graveyard of memes who’ve suffered this fate, eg $pnut $chillguy $moodeng etc. $ROUTINE is next up.

Evergreen memes survive and thrive not based on a viral moment, but rather on the meme itself being intrinsically fun and easy to meme, and having a community that loves memeing it. See $pepe, $mog, $doge etc 

$GIZMO is in the latter camp, an evergreen meme. $GIZMO takes the concept of evergreen meme, and puts it on steroids. There is nothing more evergreen than a meme that is imaginary, it gives the meme no boundaries, it makes it infinitely memeable and infinitely creative. Combining this with Fou’s ELITE/adorable/mass appealing character design is a rare and extremely potent setup for a very special memecoin. 

$GIZMO is evergreen. 🌲
